sources.name: ds_KenftsFundingGlobalCluster_target
sources.script:
source(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> ds_KenftsFundingGlobalCluster_target

typeProperties.script:
section Section1;
shared ds_KenftsFundingGlobalCluster_target = let AdfDoc = AzureStorage.BlobContents("https://pcoulibalystorageaccount.blob.core.windows.net/datakind/target/ds_KenftsFundingGlobalCluster.csv"),Csv = Csv.Document(AdfDoc, [Delimiter = ",", Encoding = TextEncoding.Utf8, QuoteStyle = QuoteStyle.Csv]), PromotedHeaders = Table.PromoteHeaders(Csv, [PromoteAllScalars = true]) in  PromotedHeaders;
shared UserQuery = let
  Source = ds_KenftsFundingGlobalCluster_target,
  #"Replaced value" = Table.ReplaceValue(Source, "", null, Replacer.ReplaceValue, {"two"}),
  #"Added custom" = Table.Profile(#"Replaced value"),
  #"Changed column type" = Table.TransformColumnTypes(#"Added custom", {{"NullCount", Int64.Type}}),
  #"Filtered rows" = Table.SelectRows(#"Changed column type", each [NullCount] = 0),
  Custom = Source,
  #"Replaced value 1" = Table.ReplaceValue(Custom, "", "Not provided", Replacer.ReplaceValue, {"countryCode"}),
  #"Replaced value 2" = Table.ReplaceValue(#"Replaced value 1", "", "Not provided", Replacer.ReplaceValue, {"clusterCode", "requirements"}),
  #"Replaced value 3" = Table.ReplaceValue(#"Replaced value 2", "", "Not provided", Replacer.ReplaceValue, {"percentFunded", "funding"}),
  #"Removed top rows" = Table.Skip(#"Replaced value 3", 1)
in
  #"Removed top rows";

sinks.name: sink2
sinks.description: Export data to ds_KenFoodPrices_dfsink. This is because HTTP won't work with dataflow. So the data sink from pipeline2 is used in the DF for transformation purposes and then sent to the same sink with a different name

dataflowSinks.name: UserQuerydsKenFoodPricesdftarget
dataflowSinks.script:
sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		date as string,
		admin1 as string,
		admin2 as string,
		market as string,
		latitude as string,
		longitude as string,
		category as string,
		commodity as string,
		unit as string,
		priceflag as string,
		pricetype as string,
		currency as string,
		price as string,
		usdprice as string
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> UserQuerydsKenFoodPricesdftarget

dataflowSinks.name: UserQueryKenftsReqFundingPQ
dataflowSinks.script:
sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		countryCode as string,
		id as string,
		name as string,
		code as string,
		typeId as string,
		typeName as string,
		startDate as string,
		endDate as string,
		year as string,
		requirements as string,
		funding as string,
		percentFunded as string
	),
	partitionFileNames:['KenftsReqFundingPQ'],
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> UserQueryKenftsReqFundingPQ
